{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01WreQxdZGqytZqCojwiScxA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the context I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` — Add validation function and call it\n\nAdd the `validateDeploymentManifest` function and insert a call to it in `getDeploymentObject`, right after the deployment is decoded from bindata and before any mutations.\n\n**New function** (add after the `caVolumeMountPath` const block, before `getDeploymentObject` or at end of file):\n\n```go\n// validateDeploymentManifest checks that the bindata deployment contains the\n// expected container and required volumes. Without the container, the update\n// helpers silently no-op and the operator would apply a deployment with stale\n// defaults.\nfunc validateDeploymentManifest(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, containerName string, requiredVolumes []string) error {\n\thasContainer := false\n\tfor _, c := range deployment.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers {\n\t\tif c.Name == containerName {\n\t\t\thasContainer = true\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif !hasContainer {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"deployment manifest missing required container %q\", containerName)\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, name := range requiredVolumes {\n\t\tfound := false\n\t\tfor _, v := range deployment.Spec.Template.Spec.Volumes {\n\t\t\tif v.Name == name {\n\t\t\t\tfound = true\n\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !found {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"deployment manifest missing required volume %q\", name)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n**Modification** in `getDeploymentObject` — add the validation call right after the deployment is decoded and before any mutations. The change is in `getDeploymentObject` at line 78, right after `deployment := decodeDeploymentObjBytes(...)`:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n\tif err := r.assertIssuerRefExists(istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to verify issuer in %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tdeployment := decodeDeploymentObjBytes(assets.MustAsset(deploymentAssetName))\n\n\t// ADD THIS BLOCK:\n\tif err := validateDeploymentManifest(deployment, istiocsrContainerName, nil); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"invalid istio-csr deployment manifest\")\n\t}\n\n\tcommon.UpdateNamespace(deployment, istiocsr.GetNamespace())\n\t// ... rest unchanged\n```\n\nThe exact edit is to insert these 3 lines after line 78 (`deployment := decodeDeploymentObjBytes(...)`) and before line 80 (`common.UpdateNamespace(...)`):\n\n```go\n\tif err := validateDeploymentManifest(deployment, istiocsrContainerName, nil); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"invalid istio-csr deployment manifest\")\n\t}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go` — Add table-driven validation test\n\nAppend this test function at the end of the file (after the closing brace of `TestUpdateVolumeWithIssuerCA`):\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidateDeploymentManifest(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname             string\n\t\tmodifyDeployment func(*appsv1.Deployment)\n\t\tcontainerName    string\n\t\trequiredVolumes  []string\n\t\twantErr          string\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:          \"valid manifest passes validation\",\n\t\t\tcontainerName: istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"missing container returns error\",\n\t\t\tmodifyDeployment: func(d *appsv1.Deployment) {\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers = []corev1.Container{\n\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"wrong-container\"},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tcontainerName: istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t\twantErr:       fmt.Sprintf(\"deployment manifest missing required container %q\", istiocsrContainerName),\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"empty containers returns error\",\n\t\t\tmodifyDeployment: func(d *appsv1.Deployment) {\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers = nil\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tcontainerName: istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t\twantErr:       fmt.Sprintf(\"deployment manifest missing required container %q\", istiocsrContainerName),\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"missing required volume returns error\",\n\t\t\tmodifyDeployment: func(d *appsv1.Deployment) {\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Spec.Volumes = []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"other-volume\"},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tcontainerName:   istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t\trequiredVolumes: []string{\"expected-volume\"},\n\t\t\twantErr:         `deployment manifest missing required volume \"expected-volume\"`,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"missing one of multiple required volumes returns error\",\n\t\t\tmodifyDeployment: func(d *appsv1.Deployment) {\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Spec.Volumes = []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"vol-a\"},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tcontainerName:   istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t\trequiredVolumes: []string{\"vol-a\", \"vol-b\"},\n\t\t\twantErr:         `deployment manifest missing required volume \"vol-b\"`,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"all required volumes present passes validation\",\n\t\t\tmodifyDeployment: func(d *appsv1.Deployment) {\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Spec.Volumes = []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"vol-a\"},\n\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"vol-b\"},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tcontainerName:   istiocsrContainerName,\n\t\t\trequiredVolumes: []string{\"vol-a\", \"vol-b\"},\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tdeployment := testDeployment()\n\t\t\tif tt.modifyDeployment != nil {\n\t\t\t\ttt.modifyDeployment(deployment)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\terr := validateDeploymentManifest(deployment, tt.containerName, tt.requiredVolumes)\n\t\t\tif tt.wantErr != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() expected error %q, got nil\", tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif err.Error() != tt.wantErr {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() error = %q, want %q\", err.Error(), tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t} else if err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() unexpected error: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Commands to verify\n\nRun from the repo root:\n\n```bash\n# Run just the new test\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/ -run TestValidateDeploymentManifest -v\n\n# Run all deployment tests to check for regressions\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/ -run TestCreateOrApplyDeployments -v\n\n# Run the full package tests\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**What changed:**\n- `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`: Added `validateDeploymentManifest(deployment, containerName, requiredVolumes)` function that checks the decoded bindata deployment has the expected container and any required volumes. Called in `getDeploymentObject` right after `decodeDeploymentObjBytes` and before any mutations, matching the trustmanager pattern. The call passes `nil` for `requiredVolumes` since the istiocsr static manifest has no volumes (volumes are added dynamically by `updateVolumeWithIssuerCA`).\n- `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go`: Added `TestValidateDeploymentManifest` with 6 table-driven cases covering: valid manifest, missing/wrong container name, empty containers, missing a required volume, missing one of multiple required volumes, and all required volumes present.\n\nThe function is parameterized (unlike the hardcoded trustmanager version) because the istiocsr bindata manifest has no static volumes — the parameter approach lets the validation logic be fully tested while the actual call site accurately reflects that no static volumes are required."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11057,"cache_read_input_tokens":88131,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_i